          },
          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Kinetic-energy distribution in the reactor neutron",
                "fission of U-232 and thermal neutron fission of Pu-241",
                "and Cm-245"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "A.Ramaswami",
                "S.Prakash",
                "S.B.Manohar",
                "S.P.Dange",
                "P.P.Venkatesan",
                "M.V.Ramaniah"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "3INDTRM"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Radiochemistry Division"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REFERENCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "J,PR/C,16,716,1977",
                "code_unit": [
                  {
                    "unit": "J,PR/C,16,716,1977",
                    "doi": "10.1103/PhysRevC.16.716",
                    "field": {
                      "reference_type": "J",
                      "reference": {
                        "code": "PR/C",
                        "number": null,
                        "volume": "16",
                        "part": null,
                        "issue": null,
                        "page": "716"
                      },
                      "date": 1977
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "institute": "3INDTRM"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " CIRUS reactor"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Thermal neutron flux of 1.4 10**13 n/(cm2s)",
                "       for 24 hours"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Activiation of first and second catcher foils",
                "were analyzed either by direct gamma counting with a",
                "Ge(Li) detector or by dissolving the foils and",
                "chemically separating the desired fission product",
                "activities employing standard radiochemical techniques."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Covered with a 7.5 mu-m superpure Al foil followed by",
                "a 25 mu-m superpure Al foil. The whole assembly was",
                "wrapped in 25 mu-m thick Al foil.",
                "* Thin uniform target of U-232:",
                "   Electrodeposited on goald coated Al foil;",
                "   The Cd cutoff ratio was approx. 0.50;",
                "   Isotopic composition:",
                "     U-232 99.14%, U-232 0.81% and U-234 0.009%.",
                "* Thin uniform target of 10 mu-g/cm2;",
                "   Electrodeposited on a gold coated Al foils;",
                "   The Cd cutoff ratio was approx 200.",
                "   The isotopic compositions:",
                "     Pu-241 80.56%, Pu-240 10.88%, Pu-239 4.77%,",
                "     Pu-242 3.78%.",
                "* Thin uniform Cm-245 target of 50 mu-g/cm2;",
                "   Electrodeposited on a gold covered Al foil;",
                "   The Cd cutoff ratio was approx 200.",
                "   The isotopic composition:",
                "     Cm-244 93.86%, Cm-246 4.13 %, Cm-245 2.01%.",
                "   As Cm-245 has (nth,f) cross section approx. 1660",
                "   times higher than that of Cm-244, 98% of the total",
                "   fission is from Cm-245."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "REC",
                "FPGAM",
                "RCHEM"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Recoil ranges were obtained from the measured",
                "activities of the fission products in the first and",
                "second catcher foil. Using the semiempirical formula",
                "by Alexander et al.(J,PR,129,1471,1963) the kinetic",
                "energy of fragment is determined from recoil ranges."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "RANGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Recoil ranges in Table I and Fig.1"
              ]
            }
          ],
